  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Sorry if this was raised before.\n\nWould it be possible to support HTTPS RPC?  Is there any reason not to?\n\nMy use case: I want to use a local node with a https based site. That is simply denied because of CORS rules (http vs https).\n\nThere is a simple call [ListenAndServeTLS](https://golang.org/pkg/net/http/#Server.ListenAndServeTLS) in the go http library, although it doesn't support the `Listener` argument as `Serve` does: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/rpc/comms/http.go#L175-l190\n",
